The paper is about a visualization system for behavior-based malware analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The system is designed to assist IT-security experts in their analysis, which involves complex data structures and requires specific interaction techniques, indicating a potential overlap with human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The system also involves knowledge representation and sharing, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the system, which could involve information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
